---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const parks = await getCollection('parks');
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the Bikepark Report — methodology and sourcing.">
  <header class="page-hero"><h1>About</h1></header>
  <div class="article-body">
    <p>
      The Bikepark Report is a researched, fully-sourced comparison of {parks.length} gravity and
      downhill mountain-bike parks reachable by car from Berlin. Each park has its own page with the
      facts that matter for planning a trip — lift, season, difficulty spread, vertical, skills
      areas, family-friendliness, and more — plus space for first-hand notes and photos.
    </p>
    <h2>How the research works</h2>
    <p>
      Every park is researched against a fixed criteria set and compiled by a dedicated research
      agent. The structured data drives the comparison table, the map, and each park page.
    </p>
    <h2>Sourcing</h2>
    <p>
      Every factual value links to at least one source — the operator's site is preferred, with
      independent directories and reviews used to cross-check. Anything that could not be verified
      is marked <span class="nf">Not found</span> rather than guessed.
    </p>
    <h2>Driving distances</h2>
    <p>
      Distances and times are computed via the Google Maps Directions API from
      Oskar-Helene-Park 7, 14195 Berlin. Confirm season and pricing on the operator's site before
      travelling.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
